[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When he had said these things,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus went out with his disciples across the Kidron Valley."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " There was an orchard"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " there, and he and his disciples went into it. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now Judas, the one who betrayed him, knew the place too, because Jesus had met there many times"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with his disciples.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Judas obtained a squad of soldiers"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and some officers of the chief priests and Pharisees."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They came to the orchard"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with lanterns"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and torches and weapons."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Jesus, because he knew everything that was going to happen to him,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came and asked them, “Who are you looking for?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Jesus the Nazarene.” He told them, “I am he.” (Now Judas, the one who betrayed him, was standing there with them.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So when Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said to them, “I am he,” they retreated"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and fell to the ground."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " asked them again, “Who are you looking for?” And they said, “Jesus the Nazarene.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I told you that I am he. If you are looking for"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " me, let these men"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " go.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He said this"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to fulfill the word he had spoken,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I have not lost a single one of those whom you gave me.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Simon Peter, who had a sword, pulled it out and struck the high priest’s slave,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " cutting off his right ear."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now the slave’s name was Malchus.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But Jesus said to Peter, “Put your sword back into its sheath! Am I not to drink the cup that the Father has given me?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then the squad of soldiers"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with their commanding officer"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the officers of the Jewish leaders"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " arrested"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus and tied him up."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " brought him first to Annas, for he was the father-in-law of Caiaphas, who was high priest that year."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now it was Caiaphas who had advised"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the Jewish leaders"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that it was to their advantage that one man die for the people.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Simon Peter and another disciple followed them as they brought Jesus to Annas."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now the other disciple"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was acquainted with the high priest, and he went with Jesus into the high priest’s courtyard.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But Simon Peter was left standing outside by the door. So the other disciple who was acquainted with the high priest came out and spoke to the slave girl who watched the door,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and brought Peter inside. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The girl"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who was the doorkeeper said to Peter, “You’re not one of this man’s disciples too, are you?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I am not.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now the slaves"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the guards"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were standing around a charcoal fire they had made, warming themselves because it was cold."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Peter also was standing with them, warming himself.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " While this was happening,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the high priest questioned Jesus about his disciples and about his teaching."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I have spoken publicly to the world. I always taught in the synagogues"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and in the temple courts,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " where all the Jewish people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " assemble together. I"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " have said nothing in secret. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Why do you ask me? Ask those who heard what I said."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " know what I said.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " had said this, one of the high priest’s officers who stood nearby struck him on the face and said,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Is that the way you answer the high priest?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “If I have said something wrong,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " confirm"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " what is wrong."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But if I spoke correctly, why strike me?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Annas sent him, still tied up,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to Caiaphas the high priest."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Meanwhile Simon Peter was standing in the courtyard"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " warming himself. They said to him, “You aren’t one of his disciples too, are you?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Peter"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " denied it: “I am not!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " One of the high priest’s slaves,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a relative of the man whose ear Peter had cut off,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said, “Did I not see you in the orchard"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with him?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Peter denied it again, and immediately a rooster crowed."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then they brought Jesus from Caiaphas to the Roman governor’s residence."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now it was very early morning.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " did not go into the governor’s residence"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so they would not be ceremonially defiled, but could eat the Passover meal. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Pilate came outside to them and said, “What accusation"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " do you bring against this man?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “If this man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were not a criminal,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " we would not have handed him over to you.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Pilate told them,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Take him yourselves and pass judgment on him"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " according to your own law!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The Jewish leaders"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “We cannot legally put anyone to death.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (This happened"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to fulfill the word Jesus had spoken when he indicated"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " what kind of death he was going to die."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ")"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Pilate went back into the governor’s residence,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " summoned Jesus, and asked him, “Are you the king of the Jews?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Are you saying this on your own initiative,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " or have others told you about me?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Pilate answered, “I am not a Jew, am I?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Your own people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and your chief priests handed you over"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to me. What have you done?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus replied, “My kingdom is not from this world. If my kingdom were from this world, my servants would be fighting to keep me from being"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " handed over"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to the Jewish authorities."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But as it is,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my kingdom is not from here.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Pilate said,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “So you are a king!” Jesus replied, “You say that I am a king. For this reason I was born, and for this reason I came into the world – to testify to the truth. Everyone who belongs to the truth listens to"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my voice.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Pilate asked,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “What is truth?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "When he had said this he went back outside to the Jewish leaders"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and announced,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I find no basis for an accusation"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " against him. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But it is your custom that I release one prisoner"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for you at the Passover."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So do you want me to release for you the king of the Jews?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then they shouted back,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Not this man,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but Barabbas!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now Barabbas was a revolutionary."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ")"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]